<setup>
  <selectFromSequence name="k" from="0.2" to="0.6" step="0.1"/>
  <selectFromSequence name="m" from="3" to="5" step="1" exclude="$z"/>
  <math name="fail"> e^(-$k*$m) </math>
  <math name="fail2"> 1 - e^(-$k*($m-1)) </math>
  <math name="z">10*$k</math>
</setup>

<p>
  The fraction of a certain type of LED light bulb that fail between time <m>t = a</m> and <m>t = b</m> (in years) is given by the definite integral 
  <me>
    \int_a^b c \, e^{-$k t} \, dt
  </me>
  for some constant <m>c</m>.
</p>  

<p>
  <ol marker="a.">
    <li>
      <p>
        Because all light bulbs eventually fail, it must be the case that 
        <me>
          \int_0^\infty c \, e^{-$k t} \, dt = 1
        </me>
        Find the value of <m>c</m> (accurate to at least <m>0.01</m>) for which this condition holds.
      </p>
      <p>
        <m>c = </m><mathInput name="cEntered"/> <answer><award><when>$cEntered=$k</when></award></answer>
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        State an integral expression whose value represents the fraction, <m>K</m>, of light bulbs that last at least <m>$m</m> years before failing.  If your integral involves the <m>\infty</m> symbol, enter <q>INF</q>.
      </p>
          <p>
            lower limit of integration: <answer name="lower">$m</answer>
          </p>
          <p>
            upper limit of integration: <answer name="upper">INF</answer>
          </p>
  
          <p>
            Integral expression for <m>K</m>, the fraction of light bulbs that last at least <m>$m</m> years before failing: 
          </p>
          <p>
            <m>K = \displaystyle\int_{$lower}^{$upper}</m><mathInput name="int1" minWidth="100" /><m>dt \, </m><answer><award><when>$int1 = $k*e^(-$k*t)</when></award></answer>
          </p>  
          <p>
            Evaluating the improper integral to an accuracy of at least <m>0.01</m>, 
          </p>     
          <p>
            <m>K = </m><mathInput name="intVal" minWidth="40" /> <answer allowedErrorInNumbers="0.01" allowedErrorIsAbsolute><award><when>$fail=$intVal </when></award></answer>
          </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        Finally, determine the fraction, <m>p</m>, of light bulbs that fail within the first <m><math simplify>$m-1</math></m> years.
      </p>
      <p>
        <m>p = </m><mathInput name="intVal2" minWidth="40" /> <answer allowedErrorInNumbers="0.01" allowedErrorIsAbsolute><award><when>$fail2=$intVal2 </when></award></answer>
      </p>
    </li>
  </ol>
</p>
  